Job Description
DUTIES:-
-Analysis and Design of Jackets and Topsides structures (inplace analysis, fatigue analysis, seismic analysis, push over analysis)
-Linear and non-linear FE analysis
-Participating in Design Review and Progress Review meeting with Clients
-Preparation of Deliverable list & Schedule, Man-hour estimate, Resource Requirement and Progress report
-Providing input to Project Planning Engineer to prepare Project Schedule
-Coordination with other departments for structural input/output data and participation in project management meetings
-Co-ordination with Clients/Contractors
-Responsible for bid/proposal input from structural
-Preparation of Design Basis Report & Technical Specification
-Standardization of Design Procedures
-Preparation of Check list and Design Guidelines
REQUIREMENTS:-
- Bachelors degree in Civil / Structural Engineering
- At least 15 years experience, with at least 12 years focussed on offshore projects
- Extensive design experience during FEED, detailed engineering and concept stages of projects
Spencer Ogden is acting as an Employment Agency in relation to this vacancy.
